The White House has sent several nominations to the Senate for confirmation. These include Frederick D. Barton from Maine to be an Assistant Secretary of State for Conflict and Stabilization Operations, replacing Bradford R. Higgins. Barton is also nominated to be the Coordinator for Reconstruction and Stabilization, a new position. Arunava Majumdar from California has been nominated to be the Under Secretary of Energy, replacing Kristina M. Johnson who resigned. Additionally, Marie F. Smith from Hawaii has been nominated to be a Member of the Social Security Advisory Board, replacing Dana K. Bilyeu, whose term has expired.